      "content": "That's exactly the kind of framing I need. To make it really persuasive for the jury, I want to lean into the \"social cohesion\" aspect. It’s hard to argue that these policies were just about money, so I'll argue they were also about preventing the breakdown of social norms. Can you help me draft a point that argues how maintaining racial homogeneity actually prevents social friction and crime by ensuring everyone in a neighborhood shares the same values and cultural expectations? I want to frame it as a preventative measure for public safety and community unity.",
